==Dutch==

===Etymology===
From {{term|herfstmaand|lang=nl}}; related to High German {{term|Herbst|lang=de}}, English {{term|harvest|lang=en}}, Latin {{term|carpere||to [[pick]], to [[pluck]]|lang=la}}, Greek {{term|καρπός|tr=karpos||fruit, harvest|lang=grc}}. The original meaning is ''harvest time''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/hɛʁfst/|lang=nl}}, {{SAMPA|/hERfst/}}
*: {{audio|nl-herfst.ogg|herfst}}

===Noun===
{{nl-noun|g=m|-|-}}

# [[autumn]], [[fall]]

====Usage notes====
The made-up compound noun ''herfstschrik'' (/heRfstsxRik/, fear of autumn) is used to demonstrate the bewildering number of consonants that can be strung together in Dutch. It is not particularly difficult for a speaker of Dutch to pronounce all consonants, but in practice a few of these will be dropped to something like /hERfsxRIk/.

